replies.body:
I think it's a nice way of saying "Thanks for contributing to Riot's efforts to remove toxicity" without all the pop-ups (although I always enjoyed logging in after a previous day's game where I had to endure a toxic player only to see the pop-up that said, "Someone you reported got punished! Thanks!" It felt good to know he got his come-uppins).

On a totally unrelated topic, are you actually in Silver? I always thought you were a higher elo... (Not that I think less of you for being silver. I'm silver myself.)

{{sticker:slayer-pantheon-thumbs}}

I totally get that, man. The ideal situation would be to do this in Season 9 after all the ranked changes come out. One game a day for the results seemed fair (as I assumed you weren't one of those guys who live streams and has time to play 10-15 games a day). With Season 9 changing the ranked experience and it being all about climbing and improving in your "off-roles", it could be interesting. You said League is more of a social thing rather than competitive... perhaps you could find yourself a duo partner or three and do the experiment in Season 9. I got a few bucks that says you'd end up in mid-to-high Gold by the end of it...

If you ever decide to do it, post the results here please!

{{sticker:sg-ahri-2}}
